    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE COOLANT TEMPERATURE GAUGE</title>
        <para>The engine coolant temperature is sensed by an electrical sending unit that sends a voltage to the ECM.
            The ECM converts the voltage into a digital signal. This signal is transferred, via the data link, to the
            microprocessor in the instrument cluster. The microprocessor drives the temperature gauge.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
